title I/O Handler Read/Write Pipeline

|Caller|
start
fork
  :Call **easy_io.load**(file, file_format?, backend_args?, fast_backend?);
  |easy_io Dispatcher|
  :Infer **file_format** from file extension\nif not explicitly provided;
  if (format in **file_handlers** registry?) then (no)
    #FFB3B3:Raise **TypeError**\n(unsupported format);
    stop
  else (yes)
    :Lookup handler = **file_handlers[file_format]**\n//(JsonHandler / YamlHandler / PickleHandler\n// NumpyHandler / TorchHandler / TarHandler\n// GzipHandler / JsonlHandler / CsvHandler\n// PandasHandler / PILHandler / ImageioVideoHandler / TxtHandler)//;
    if (file is **str path**?) then (yes)
      |FileBackend|
      :Resolve backend via\n**get_file_backend**(file, backend_args,\nenable_singleton=True);
      |easy_io Dispatcher|
      if (handler.**str_like** == True?) then (yes)
        |FileBackend|
        :Fetch text: **file_backend.get_text**(file);
        |easy_io Dispatcher|
        :Wrap in **StringIO**(text);
      else (no)
        if (**fast_backend** == True?) then (yes)
          |FileBackend|
          :Fetch bytes: **file_backend.fast_get**(file);
        else (no)
          |FileBackend|
          :Fetch bytes: **file_backend.get**(file);
        endif
        |easy_io Dispatcher|
        :Wrap in **BytesIO**(bytes);
      endif
      |Format Handler|
      :Execute **handler.load_from_fileobj**(fileobj, **kwargs);
    else (no)
      if (file has **.read** method?\n//file-like object//) then (yes)
        |Format Handler|
        :Execute **handler.load_from_fileobj**(file, **kwargs);
      else (other)
        |easy_io Dispatcher|
        #FFB3B3:Raise **TypeError**\n(invalid file argument);
        stop
      endif
    endif
    |easy_io Dispatcher|
    :Return **deserialized object** to caller;
    |Caller|
    :Receive deserialized data;
  endif

fork again
  :Call **easy_io.dump**(obj, file, file_format?, backend_args?, fast_backend?);
  |easy_io Dispatcher|
  :Infer **file_format** from file extension\nif not explicitly provided;
  if (file is None AND no file_format?) then (yes)
    #FFB3B3:Raise **ValueError**\n(cannot infer format);
    stop
  else (no)
  endif
  if (format in **file_handlers** registry?) then (no)
    #FFB3B3:Raise **TypeError**\n(unsupported format);
    stop
  else (yes)
    :Lookup handler = **file_handlers[file_format]**;
    if (file is **None**?) then (yes)
      |Format Handler|
      :Execute **handler.dump_to_str**(obj, **kwargs)\n//Serialize to string/bytes, no I/O//;
      note right
        **TorchHandler** and **TarHandler**
        raise NotImplementedError here
      end note
      |easy_io Dispatcher|
      :Return serialized **string/bytes** to caller;
      |Caller|
      :Receive serialized data;
    else (no)
      if (file is **str path**?) then (yes)
        |FileBackend|
        :Resolve backend via\n**get_file_backend**(file, backend_args,\nenable_singleton=True);
        |easy_io Dispatcher|
        if (handler.**str_like** == True?) then (yes)
          |Format Handler|
          :Create **StringIO**();
          :Execute **handler.dump_to_fileobj**(obj, f, **kwargs);
          |FileBackend|
          :Write text: **file_backend.put_text**(f.getvalue(), file);
        else (no)
          |Format Handler|
          :Create **BytesIO**();
          :Execute **handler.dump_to_fileobj**(obj, f, **kwargs);
          |easy_io Dispatcher|
          if (**fast_backend** == True?) then (yes)
            |FileBackend|
            :Write bytes: **file_backend.fast_put**(f, file)\n//(fallback to put if unsupported)//;
          else (no)
            |FileBackend|
            :Write bytes: **file_backend.put**(f, file);
          endif
        endif
      else (no)
        if (file has **.write** method?\n//file-like object//) then (yes)
          |Format Handler|
          :Execute **handler.dump_to_fileobj**(obj, file, **kwargs);
        else (other)
          |easy_io Dispatcher|
          #FFB3B3:Raise **TypeError**\n(invalid file argument);
          stop
        endif
      endif
      |Caller|
      :Object persisted to destination;
    endif
  endif
end fork

|Caller|
stop

note as N1
  **Handler Registry (file_handlers dict)**
  ──────────────────────────────────────
  json            → JsonHandler (str_like=True)
  yaml / yml      → YamlHandler (str_like=True)
  txt             → TxtHandler  (str_like=True)
  csv             → CsvHandler  (str_like=True)
  jsonl           → JsonlHandler (str_like=True)
  pandas          → PandasHandler
  pickle / pkl    → PickleHandler (str_like=False)
  npy             → NumpyHandler  (str_like=False)
  pt / pth / ckpt → TorchHandler  (str_like=False)
  jit             → TorchJitHandler
  tar             → TarHandler    (str_like=False)
  gz              → GzipHandler   (str_like=False)
  jpg/jpeg/png... → PILHandler
  mp4/avi/mov...  → ImageioVideoHandler (str_like=False)
  ──────────────────────────────────────
  Custom handlers registered via
  @register_handler(file_formats) decorator
end note

@enduml
